tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), indicating prediabetes. Renal function, electrolytes, and glucose are normal. Recommend monitoring glycemic control and considering lifestyle modifications to prevent progression to diabetes. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
